			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>The twisting issue shouldn't be a discussion of whether it was intended or not.&nbsp; It is no longer optional to twist.&nbsp; You must&nbsp;if you want to be welcome in any group.&nbsp; You must while soloing as the alternative - maintaining only a single buf, is unacceptable.&nbsp; Other classes can cast a buf and it will remain for up to 4 hours, so&nbsp;Bards should be permitted to maintain a few bufs at once. &nbsp; Bards should be able to twist as many songs as they like using an automated interface provided by SOE.&nbsp; The interface is a list of the songs you currently want to twist.&nbsp; Only 3 songs (bufs) will be maintained at once due to song duration and casting time.&nbsp; I should also be able to interrupt the twist macro and switch to another song at any time when the situation demands it.&nbsp; This constant button pushing is unwarranted and can't be supported by any logical debate, hence the 'SILENCE' from the developers.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If constant button pushing is the standard, then take away the melee auto attack.&nbsp;&nbsp; Let them mash a button every time they want to attack.&nbsp;&nbsp; See how they would like it.&nbsp; Also take out the auto follow command.&nbsp;&nbsp;People could be away from the keyboard using this 'cheat'.&nbsp;&nbsp; Face it, there is discrimation against Bards from ancient times, and Rangers more recently, that has to be corrected.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bard is still a favourite class foof mine&nbsp;because&nbsp;they don't use up mana singing songs leading to medding and they are able to sing while moving.&nbsp;&nbsp; The diversity of game play available is another favourite of mine.&nbsp; So why do I play other classes while my 65 Bard gathers dust?&nbsp; You guessed it, too much button pushing interfering with the social interaction.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Oh yeah, since you're already thinking it, don't even consider making bard improvements available only after investing more&nbsp;AA points.&nbsp; I'm so sick of this approach to fixing class problems.&nbsp; I figure you do it&nbsp;because you aren't creative enough to think of something new to add but needed to fill up the list of advancements.&nbsp; I certainly don't consider it a fair reward for the time sink to get what I should have anyway.&nbsp; Example:&nbsp; fizzle rates increased on songs so that the fizzle reduction AA could be seen as useful.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have one for you - you try to charge my credit card but your transaction fizzles, better luck next time.</DIV>
																		
