<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>but the discussion here is twisting causing problems.&nbsp; yeah i've played my bard for four years now.. love him.&nbsp; always come back to him (yes.. i switch to other classes when they 1) break bards after a patch 2) my hands hurt 3) they nerf abilities which SET BARDS APART (ie lull being nerfed to like 30 seconds).)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>should SOE put in an autotwisting sequence?&nbsp; hell yes.&nbsp; should it only be 3 songs?&nbsp; no.&nbsp; i can "comfortably" twist four.&nbsp; it should be four.&nbsp; should this UI take into account songs with longer durations?&nbsp; yes.&nbsp; so... if i'm twisting katta's song of sword dancing.. i should be able to twist five.&nbsp; should i be able to use clickies at the same time?&nbsp; yes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>so.. my lute of the flowing waters... + autosequence... gives me 5-6 songs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>another issue, while we're at it... is magical effects (ie procs, boastful bellow) interupting item clickies.&nbsp; for example: i'm singing selos with my pants... i hit boastful bellow.. it interupts.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>while this is no big deal... imagine this scenario:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>my friend bard has a composer's chestplate.&nbsp; she uses it to sing warsong.&nbsp; so... she's twisting along... clicks her bp.... it's midcast and she procs.&nbsp; **I love Brenlo!** her song ends.&nbsp; see the problem here?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>basically... the problem is that while we're treated like casters not-at-all... we have a lot of deficiencies due to programming oriented toward casters, and simple "fixes" for the bard abilities.&nbsp; we can stop a song by reclicking it... but the program can't tell the difference between a spell effect due to proc or aa, and a song.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>we can twist songs.. but not talk, react quickly, etc.&nbsp; after a while... i have to stop playing.&nbsp; my hands hurt... i'm frustrated from all the missed notes.... and people drop from my friends list like flies because well.. i'm not talking to them so we lose contact.&nbsp; why not talk to them?&nbsp; oh sorry... i'm busy barding.</DIV>
