			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>This is a good idea, allowing bards to have mulitiple songs going does NOT create any imbalance, but instead, solves one.&nbsp; A cleric can cast multiple spells one time, lasting up to 3+ hours at the longest.&nbsp; Shaman buffs go 30-90+ minutes, Druids too, and debuffs from Druids, Necro's, Shaman and DD and DoTs&nbsp;from all of the above and Magicians and Chanters all out-class the Bards ability. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Example, Shaman can cast multiple spells (6-8), med up with the benefit of Kei in 2-3 min, and rock on.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The Bard can only provide 1-2 (max 3 if your wrist is up to it) songs without any extended duration.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Giving the Bard the ability to start and end&nbsp;a song and have the benefits of the song last for several&nbsp;minutes instead of a few seconds&nbsp;wouldnt hurt anything.&nbsp; Just cap the number of songs individuals can have to 3 or 4 songs and you not only remove the potential wrist injuries, but make the Bard class far more effective without imbalancing the game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also it would be hard to abuse this, bard songs only apply to those who are grouped with the bard, and in the direct vicinity of the bard anyhow.</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
