												Personally, if they REALLY wanted to fix bards, I would like to see a queue window for bards.  Drag and drop spells into a queue.  Have a button beside it to goggle the Queue on or off.  Like that if i'm doing say Grp songs, i can turn it on and do meelee while chatting.  Have it able to turn off in case i need to say use another song...  <br>Steps to do this:<br>1) Make a 9th spell gem for the queue (say 3 songs max).<br>2) Beside the gem would be actually 3 gems side by side.<br>3) Clicking gem 9 stops the autotwist.<br>4) Clicking any 1-8 gem also stops autotwist (same as if you click a spell gem to interrupt current song now.<br>5) You can drag and drop gems from 1-8 to each queue gem.<br><br>That would be the SIMPLEST fix in the world.<br><br>Another thing: Code the queue so that if we only put 2 spells in it, it has a lower miss notes chance, and of course 1 song only you'd not miss as no recast.<br><br>Heck charge aa's for the extra spell gem...you could even say put a limit to only 2 slots could be damage song (snare dd etc)...it'd still be a lifesaver.  <br><br>ALT+C window allows drag and drop and separate timers for keys, I would assume you could do the same basic thing with songs and have a very very nice working version of the above.
																		
