						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Nostromo n50</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>remap secondary hotkeys for cast slots for your songs to f9-f12. remap those functions to alt+f9-f12.</DIV>
<DIV>open write macro</DIV>
<DIV>hit f9,f10,f10,f11,f11,f12,f12,f9</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>insert 3.05 second delay after first f9, .05 second after second f9 and first f10. rinse and repeat. set to repeat forever. however, missed notes will&nbsp;let you go maybe 5 times.</DIV>
<DIV>make a button for stop&nbsp;macro.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hey look, an autotwisting bard.</DIV>
<DIV><BR>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I figured that out in 5 minutes. How about the designers at&nbsp;SOE figure out something that works that well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>pros: save your wrist. lets you talk (aka, enjoy the game, keep your group informed with what you are pulling/mezzing/gating/fading )</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>cons: sucks that you can't add in clickies, and you have to restart with every missed note, and it doesn't work with high lag.&nbsp;cost of the controller, running more software (eq is kinda intensive, and you don't have a midline or better machine, you will be hurting)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For the record, if you added autotwist that worked like that, you wouldn't have to worry about the 3 mezzed mobs thing, cause it RECASTS every time the song pulses, just like if you were doing it manually, so you would have to switch targets every time to make it land on the right mob.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I like to keep my 5-7 songs up, and it is not real condusive to that. I can use it, but choose not to. It really is not worth the trouble. So, there you go, I solved autotwisting. And you couldn't really use that to do the massive ae kiting that caused the nerf on bard extended notes, due to bard missed notes. It just won't work.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I love my class, but we have got to be one of the most underdesigned and tested classes. Not bashing the desing team, but for something like this, unless you have played a bard for 50 plus days worth of playing time, you don't, and can't, have a real appreciation for how big of a pain in the butt being a bard can be.</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
