												<DIV>Ok, I have a bard, I like&nbsp; my bard, and I completely understand the problems with twisting for hours and hours in ldon's and such.</DIV>
<DIV>However, I think I may have an idea for the Dev's&nbsp;and even us should you want to listen.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Change to the current sytem...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As melee's do not recieve a mana bar.. Image in we recieved a "spell gem bar" that only contained 4 icons...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>now - extend both the Effect time and the Recast time of the "song/spell"...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Imagine, if all songs worked similar to the 2 and 1/2 minute selo's but also had a 2 and 1/2 minute recast time (or 2 min and 20 seconds?)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>only 4 spell gems.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This way they become similar to "buffs" and remove the trouble of recasting over and over and over and over in a row, they free us up,</DIV>
<DIV>and as they do not last as long as "normal buffs" the abuse is minimal.&nbsp; Unless a bard wants to constantly be sitting down, changing out</DIV>
<DIV>songs, casting again, sitting down, changing up songs... as this idea is not intended this way, it still provides the player with an alternet means.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Dot's and such could be adjusted accordingly.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Again, recast time is much much much longer, but removes the need to constantly twist.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is only a suggestion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kaymaliki</DIV>
																		
