			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 163 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_1.gif' border=0 alt='1 rating - 1.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I read this thread because I was curious to hear what the Devs had to say on the subject of macros, but I have to point something out.&nbsp; They must be doing something right at Sony because every class comes to the boards to whine about how unfair it is to them.&nbsp; Our enchanter boards are loaded with them.&nbsp; Sometimes I think people want to have it work like that episode of the Simpsons where Sideshow Bob jumps into an F-18 (or whatever it is) and the only control on the dash is a button marked "Fly".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My enchanter can't insti-mez while moving, keep a mez on while the mob is dotted, instantly recast upon failure and can't wear plate to help keep him alive for&nbsp;mez fail aggro.&nbsp; And we are supposed to be best at crowd control.&nbsp;&nbsp;And how much mana do those songs chew up so you can't play them for a few minutes while you build it back up?&nbsp; How many groups would take a chanter over you in GoD?&nbsp; So please cut the poor bards talk, it makes you look bad, and it saps your credibility, even when you are otherwise right.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now having said that, (and I am guessing lowering much faction)&nbsp;I think there should be some kind of relief from all the button pushing.&nbsp; I do not think they should allow 3rd party macros at all, but they should work on the functionality of hot keys or function keys to make it easier to do the song twisting.&nbsp; Whether or not they intended to let you twist songs or not isn't really the issue in my view.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bards are going to twist as many songs as possible to be as absolutely as effective as possible, even if it takes away their ability to chat or leads to player injury.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>To that end, maybe a function key that will work more than one hot button?&nbsp; So intead of pressing 11232341 in rapid succession, how about something that allows the sequence to be mapped to a hotkey (within limits) to take the button presses down from 8 in my example to say 3?&nbsp; I don't see this as unbalancing (it still requires some attention) but will significantly enhance the game experience for the player.&nbsp; </DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>Ol' Hoss <br><br>"..and a thousand thousand slimy things lived on and so did I"<br>From The Rhyme of the Ancient Mariner
