									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 32 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_4.gif' border=0 alt='1 rating - 4.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>First i am a bit confused, I have always thought twisting is one of the distinquising traits of a Bard. I can't see why someone would want to&nbsp;effectively reduce it's uniqueness and benifits. Here is my concern and suggestion</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>First making twisting compeltely automatic really takes allot away from those playing the class as far as prestige. There is no dobt that those that play this class well can twist 4 songs but many can't. To all of a sudden give everyone that ability would be the same as giving every caster their chaos spells when they hit the required lvl. It just makes the class that much less impressive and also reduces there value in my opion. Right now i know if i see a bard only twisting 2 songs i know what to expect from them. If all of a sudden everyone can do it there isn't a good way to judge there abilities till they do a bad pull or bad CC and get everyone killed. Though i do agree it does suck having to constantly turn the songs on and off,&nbsp;I have to wonder how many bards didn't know that when they started. Some customizing to make it easier on the one hands would be nice, but i do think if you want to run more then one song at a time you should have to make an effort to do it, after all that is really a judge of how good of a bard you are. To this same extent i also wouldn't want to limit someone that can find a way to achieve more then 4 songs at a time.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>With that said there may also be another suggestion that isn't mentioned yet but is already being implemented in EQ2. Something along the line of a concentration limitation. Where a bard only has 20 pts and therefore can only play songs that don't add up to a concetration over 20. Then maybe items that allow that number to increase.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Please understand this is just a suggestion from Mage not bard. I know i don't understand the intricatcies of a bard, but i know there are allot of things you can do i would never dream of ( a bard friend has a plan on how to pull an entire zone and get a whole lvl in about 30 min). There is no doubt that twisting is a big issue and i agree that making it simpler is surely in order but to completely remove it is a bit drastic since it is so important to the class in my view. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Good luck on getting this resolved</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
